message.content: A 'Papilio eurymedon' is a species of butterfly that belongs to the family Papilionidae. The wings of this butterfly are broad and are characterized by black-colored veins. The forewing is predominantly black with a few white spots, while the hindwing is primarily yellow with black spots. The body of the 'Papilio eurymedon' is covered with hairy-like scales and is generally black in color. The butterfly has a wingspan of around 7.6-10.2 cm. 'Papilio eurymedon' is primarily found in the western region of North America, including California and Oregon. This butterfly typically inhabits open forests, streambeds, and canyons. 'Papilio eurymedon' is a pollinator and is considered to be an important species in the ecosystem.
